article.headline: Mount St. Mary's defeats Canisius 74-69
article.description: — George Tinsley had 18 points in Mount St. Mary's 74-69 win over Canisius on Friday night.
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- — George Tinsley had 18 points in Mount St. Mary's 74-69 win over Canisius on Friday night. Tinsley also added seven rebounds for the Mountaineers (6-8, 2-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Dakota Leffew scored 12 points and added seven rebounds. Dallas Hobbs shot 4 for 9, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. Tre Dinkins led the Golden Griffins (6-7, 1-2) in scoring, finishing with 18 points. Frank Mitchell added 13 points and 11 rebounds for Canisius. Siem Uijtendaal also had 12 points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
